## Conventions

### Naming
- [e.g., camelCase for variables, PascalCase for classes]
- [e.g., kebab-case for file names]
- [e.g., UPPER_SNAKE for constants and env vars]

### Structure
- [e.g., src/ for source, tests/ for tests]
- [e.g., One module per file, max 500 lines]
- [e.g., Migrations in db/migrations/V{n}__description.sql]

### Git
- [e.g., Conventional Commits: type(scope): subject]
- [e.g., Branch naming: type/TICKET-description]
- [e.g., Squash merge to main, preserve commits on feature branches]

## Critical Rules

### Always
- [e.g., Always validate user input at API boundaries]
- [e.g., Always use parameterized queries (never string interpolation)]
- [e.g., Always write tests for new features before merging]

### Never
- [e.g., Never commit secrets (.env, credentials, API keys)]
- [e.g., Never use eval() or dynamic code execution]
- [e.g., Never deploy without CI passing]

